FBIS4-38675 "drsov106_p_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 CAUCASUS Armenia Abolishes Moscow Mission, Appoints Envoy Abolishes Moscow Mission, Appoints Envoy NC0106172494 Yerevan Radio Yerevan International Service in Armenian 1600 GMT 1 Jun 94 NC0106172494 Yerevan Radio Yerevan International Service Armenian BFN [Text] The Armenian Republic President Levon Ter-Petrosyan signed a decree today to abolish the Armenian Government's Permanent Mission in the Russian Federation and instructed the Armenian Government to take action to implement this decree. The Armenian president also signed decrees appointing Yuriy Mkrtumyan Armenia's ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary to Russia and bestowing upon him the diplomatic title of ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary.
